{
  "stem": "3524.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I'd say that we had a general mix of the population you might find in any major city in the United States.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We received extensive training both in the field and in the hospital setting.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Mostly we were trained to set up the tents-- show how we could operate the equipment in the field.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were given-- oh, how do I want to say the-- imaginary patients that we treated on a evacuation process.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we were tested by surgical inspector groups to determine our fitness to take care of the patients as they came in.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In the meantime, as a pharmacist, I worked in the dispensary and assisted in the sick call and the treatment of the minor ailments that we were able to treat within the company.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By the time we finished our training, I think we all felt quite competent in being able to perform our jobs.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had 40 medical officers in our unit.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had section chiefs.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Each medical officer worked with a section.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Ours happened to be pharmacy, lab, and x-ray.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we had a Captain Morton, who was our section chief for-- for the section.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then we had one lieutenant who was the x-ray technician-- x-ray expert.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I left on my 21st birthday [LAUGHS] on the It was a rather emotional setting.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think we were all in a way anxious, and yet anticipating what might be forthcoming in the next few months.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I think most of us were ready and willing to go.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think we had some solace in the fact that we were-- had confidence in our training and would be able to perform our job well.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
